sentences: Hilde Hefte (born 1 September 1956 in Kristiansand, Norway) is a Norwegian jazz singer.
She played saxophone and clarinet for ten years when she was young, as an apprentice to her father who was saxophone teacher and musician.
During a period of some years she was also teaching music at Agder musikkonservatorium before she started as a full-time musician.
Her debut solo album Round Chet's Midnight was released in 1999, and received great reviews, like Down Beat Magazine: "She's making waves on the Norwegian scene.
